# SkillMentor Backend Architecture Rules

When Adding a New Module (e.g., Payment, Review), you MUST follow this checklist:

- [ ] Create **Entity** with dual-key if Clerk-linked, `@CreationTimestamp`/`@UpdateTimestamp`, `Serializable`
- [ ] Create **RequestDTO** with Bean Validation; **ResponseDTO** with only what the client needs
- [ ] Create **Service interface** (in `services/`) with response DTO return types
- [ ] Create **ServiceImpl** (in `services/impl/`) with `SkillMentorException` wrapping, `@Cacheable`, Slf4j logging
- [ ] Create **Repository** extending `JpaRepository<Entity, IdType>`; add only needed custom queries
- [ ] Create **Controller** extending `AbstractController`, `@Validated`, mapping with `ModelMapper` moved to service
- [ ] Apply `@PreAuthorize` at class and method level; implement ownership checks
- [ ] Register any custom `ModelMapper` type maps in `ModelMapperConfig`
- [ ] Add cache `value` name to cache configuration if using Redis

### Example: ReviewModule skeleton
```text
entities/Review.java
dto/ReviewRequestDTO.java
dto/response/ReviewResponseDTO.java
services/ReviewService.java
services/impl/ReviewServiceImpl.java
repositories/ReviewRepository.java
controllers/ReviewController.java extends AbstractController
```
